    Sleep in the hospital is different. It’s lighter. Fragmented.
    Sometimes it doesn’t come at all.
  </p>

  <p>
    What helped some families:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>Eye masks and earplugs — even imperfect ones help</li>
    <li>Asking staff when alarms can be minimized</li>
    <li>Accepting rest, not sleep, on the hardest nights</li>
  </ul>

